abstract: Critics and writers for The New York Times catalog some of the more promising options for chasing a dream or a feeling or someone to help absolve you of all your yesterdays.
snippet: Critics and writers for The New York Times catalog some of the more promising options for chasing a dream or a feeling or someone to help absolve you of all your yesterdays.
lead_paragraph: PEOPLE don’t go out on New Year’s Eve in anticipation of a great new year. They go out to erase 300-some-odd days of demons and to squeeze in a few more before the ball drops and forces reassessment. It’s a night in which everyone gets a free pass for misbehavior, because the next morning, society insists that you’re born anew.

abstract: Nordic Preserves, Fish & Wildlife is an unusual addition to the Essex Street Market on the Lower East Side.
snippet: Nordic Preserves, Fish & Wildlife is an unusual addition to the Essex Street Market on the Lower East Side.
lead_paragraph: Nordic Preserves, Fish & Wildlife, a pale wooden stall announced by a caribou head on one wall, is an unusual addition to the Essex Street Market on the Lower East Side. Annika Sundvik, above, and her partners, John Lavelle and Lu Rapunil, specialize in Scandinavian foods, offering house-made items like herring in an array of marinades, like citrus and hot curry, gravlax, meatballs, sauces, pickles and potted game. (The cooking is done at the other Nordic Preserves location, in La Marqueta in Harlem.) Imported cakes, candies, cheeses, flatbreads and condiments like shrimp paste are also available. Ms. Sundvik, who was an owner of Good World Bar & Grill, White Slab Palace and Fisk, will pour free glogg on Sunday, in celebration of the shop’s opening earlier in the week.

abstract: The bride and groom were law clerks at the Supreme Court, where they met.
snippet: The bride and groom were law clerks at the Supreme Court, where they met.
lead_paragraph: Erin Fielding Delaney and Travis Dean Lenkner were married Saturday in New York. Judge Guido Calabresi of the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit, whose chambers are in New Haven, officiated at the New York Yacht Club.
